doc.after: In 1945, Alaska Airlines hired its first stewardesses.[11] In 1947, James Wooten became president of the airline and he began to expand the airline greatly.[11][12] Under his leadership, the company purchased many surplus military aircraft from the government that were used during World War II. The airline purchased Douglas DC-3s, Douglas DC-4s, and Curtiss-Wright C-46 Commandos.[8] Alaska Airlines was the first carrier certified to operate DC-3s on skis.[10]
